	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Emulators look nothing like what a real NES does on a HDTV when hooked up with a rf cable. A real NES has every other scan-line offset one  pixel from the other. Do any emulators do that? Certainly most do not - yet this is the actual intended view of the graphics.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


